block content

  +state('Ohio', '/assets/images/flag-ohio.svg', 'The Buckeye State', 'March 1, 1803')

  .intro
    p The Ohio flag is unlike any other U.S. flag due to its unique shape. It’s the only flag that isn’t a rectangle and is instead a swallow-tailed burgee.
    p It was designed by Cleveland architect John Eisenmann in 1901 for the Pan-American Exposition in New York, created to fly over the Ohio Building.
    p The flag was officially adopted May 9, 1902.

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Flag design
      p The Ohio flag is burgee-shaped featuring three red and two white horizontal stripes. A blue triangular field extends from the left edge, its apex at the center of the middle red stripe. 
      p Upon the blue triangle, a red disc is placed at the center of a larger white circle. Seventeen white five-pointed stars surround.
    .visual.flag
      img(src='/assets/images/flag-ohio.svg')

  .guide.wide
    .content
      h2 Iconography
      ul.visual.icon-list
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-ohio-icon-burgee.svg')
          h4 Burgee
          p Eisenmann described the triangles of the burgee representing the hills and valleys of the Ohio landscape.
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-ohio-icon-stripes.svg')
          h4 Stripes
          p The stripes similarly represent the Ohio rivers and roadways.
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-ohio-icon-circle.svg')
          h4 Circles
          p The circles represent two things: the “O” of Ohio and the buckeye, the nut that falls from the buckeye tree (and from which Ohio gets its nickname).
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-ohio-icon-stars.svg')
          h4 Stars
          p The 13 stars to the left represent the original 13 colonies and the other four represent Vermont, Kentucky, Tennessee, and Ohio, the states that followed.

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Colors
      p The Ohio flag #[em is] similar to other U.S. flags in its colors, utilizing the classic red, white, and blue.
    .visual.colors.primary
      .color
        .sample(class='us-blue')
        .name Blue
        .hex #001c5a
      .color
        .sample(class='us-red')
        .name Red
        .hex #c30a3a
      .color
        .sample(class='white')
        .name White
        .hex #ffffff

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Production
      p John Eisenmann obtained a U.S. patent for his Ohio flag design and created detailed specification diagrams, simplified and recreated here.
      p The flag has an 8:13 proportion.
      p Many flag makers, rather than create the Ohio flag’s unique shape, print the Ohio flag on a rectangular field of white.
    .visual
      img(src='/assets/images/flag-ohio-dimensions.svg')

